In the 1980s I spent several summers in Italy. This biscotti is often given as a breakfast food or mid-day snack. They are simple and delicious and were not sold in the US back then. They are so good that I brought back two bags from a recent trip to Italy. It is great to see that they may now be found on Amazon!

Note: it is great to open a bag, smell the contents, pour a glass of milk, then dip the Macines in the milk. Great routine and treat for kids!

They have had many complaints of a similar nature. This, they claimed, also reduced the crystal size. They said this problem should go away with their newer crop. I have used and liked Sugar in the Raw for many years, after being introduced to it in a Starbucks. My most recent purchase, however, was the very sweet caramelized sugar. I like to use something in a cup and in a piece of paper until the sugar has melted, then spooning it through and through, until it bubbles. My favorite flavor of this recipe is the buttery tangy tang! You can taste the caramel over the sugar, then you can just rub it into your favorite pie filling with vanilla.

The key to this recipe is the combination of this sugar, the honey, and the vanilla. You will not have to wait, as both honey and the sugar will melt in a single swallow. We love your product and want you to change to no-burn harvesting so we can continue to buy it, knowing we aren't contributing to Global Warming and lung disease.
